  "prompt": "How has legislation evolved to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Legislation to combat money laundering has evolved significantly over the past few decades:\n\n1. Early Stages\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970, USA)\n- First international recognition of money laundering as a criminal offense\n\n2. Key Milestones\n- FATF establishment (1989)\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime (2000)\n- USA PATRIOT Act (2001)\n- Enhanced international cooperation\n- Stricter reporting requirements\n\n3. Regulatory Developments\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Enhanced financial institution compliance standards\n\n4. Technology Impact\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Advanced algorithmic detection\n- Blockchain and cryptocurrency tracking mechanisms\n\n5. Recent Trends\n- Increased international information sharing\n- Broader definition of money laundering\n- Stricter penalties\n- More comprehensive compliance frameworks\n- Focus on beneficial ownership transparency\n\n6. Current Challenges\n- Cryptocurrencies\n- Complex international financial networks\n- Emerging technological laundering techniques\n\nThe legislative approach has progressively become more comprehensive, technologically advanced, and internationally coordinated.",
